The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 22 September is 3,321 (384.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 18 September, there were 107 new confirmed cases (12.4 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 11 September, there were 127 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 16% (20 fewer cases).
